%e A014557 Any 2-coloring of the edges of K_6 produces at least two monochromatic triangles.  Having colors induce K_3,3 and 2K_3 shows this is attained, so a(6) = 2.
%p A014557 A049322 := proc(n) local u; if n mod 2 = 0 then u := n/2; RETURN(u*(u-1)*(u-2)/3); elif n mod 4 = 1 then u := (n-1)/4; RETURN(u*(u-1)*(4*u+1)*2/3); else u := (n-3)/4; RETURN(u*(u+1)*(4*u-1)*2/3); fi; end;
%t A014557 Table[Binomial[n,3] - Floor[n/2*Floor[((n-1)/2)^2]],{n,0,100}] (* _Alexander Adamchuk_, Nov 29 2006 *)
